					<head>Baʽal ha-Ṭurim</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046 lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" rend="visible">
						<summary>Midrash on the Pentateuch</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible">
							<title xml:lang="he">בעל הטורים</title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Baʽal ha-Ṭurim</title>
							<note>
								<p>Midrash on the five books of the Torah.</p>
								<p>Incomplete at the beginning.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">" ... נשלם מדקש חמשה חומשי תורה בעזרת אל גדול גבור ... יום חמישי דהוא עשרין ותלתא [יומין לחודש] טבת שנת א'תתקס"ג ש[ני]ן לשטרי במאתא ... ונכתב עלי שם החבר הטוב ... דוד בן זכריה הידוע אלידאעי ... והכותב ... דוד בן סעדיא בן דוד הידוע אלטייאני".<locus from="202r" to="202v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Oriental paper.</support>
								<extent>202 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>148</height>
										<width>102</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>115/120</height>
										<width>70/75</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p> folios (+ 1 unfoliated modern flyleaf at the beginning and 1 unfoliated modern and 1 older flyleaf at the end)).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Indeterminable (binding too tight).</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Paper is patched; first 6 leaves are on guards.</p>
									<p>Water damage.</p>
									<p>Silk gauze on folio 1.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1">
									<p>Marginal notes.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">The scribe's name is given in the colophon: Daṿid ben Saadia ben Daṿid.</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<decoDesc>
							<decoNote>
								<p>Ornamental parashah signs (e.g. folios 78v, 93v, 106r, 127v, 139r, 148r, 163v, 168r).</p>
								<p>Decorated initial words at the beginning of Exodus and Leviticus (folios 62v, 114r, 141v, 176r).</p>
							</decoNote>
						</decoDesc>
